The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 January is 34,584 (4,002.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 January, there were 3,288 new confirmed cases (380.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 January, there were 4,546 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 28% (1,258 fewer cases).
